axis: cancellation-transitions
status: pending-spec
needs: target-neutral public cancellation states, transition ordering, one-shot interaction, and exact diagnostic
expected: Intentionally unspecified. The semantic owner requires cancellation evidence
  but has not frozen whether cancellation races before/after a resume claim, how a
  cancelled reusable continuation reports later resumes, or the portable diagnostic.
  This harness must not become the accidental owner by inventing those rules.
proposal: A non-binding option is on the table for the semantic owner in
  specs/durable-cancellation-proposal.md (recommended answers to all three open
  questions, reusing the frozen atomic one-shot claim + typed-failure models). It flips
  nothing and changes no reference code; this vector stays pending-spec until the owner
  ratifies, amends, or rejects it.
